The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Gurgaon, Aug. 18 (PTI): Neelam Mahajan, who filed an assault case against cricketer Yuvraj Singh and his mother, was arrested today for contempt of court after she accused a magistrate of bias and improper handling of the case. She was released after she apologised.

 Neelam had filed a complaint last December, alleging that Yuvraj and his mother assaulted her son at the cricketers birthday party.

 Mumbai (PTI): Amitabh Bachchan has alleged that his power of attorney was misused to buy a property in Barbanki district. He had given the power to one Vinay Shukla from Allahabad on the basis of some papers which turned out to be fake, the actors application to police said.

 Toronto (PTI): Canadian authorities will issue an apology and travel documents to three Sikh children whose passport applications were rejected as they were wearing religious headgear in the photographs, an official said on Saturday.

 Shivpuri (PTI): A government school principal has been suspended for allegedly harassing a Dalit student because a button on her uniform was missing. Brajesh Kumar Sharma allegedly forced the Class VI girl to open her shirt in front of other students.

 New Delhi (PTI): The CBI has sent a notice to Dera Sacha Sauda chief Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh to appear before an Ambala court on August 31 in connection with chargesheets, including that of sexual exploitation, filed against him.




